Package info.oais.infomodel.implementation

Class DataObjectRefImpl

java.lang.Object
info.oais.infomodel.implementation.DataObjectRefImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
DigitalObjectRefImpl
public class DataObjectRefImpl extends Object implements DataObject
Reference implementation of DataObject. The DataObject has an Identifier, so that it can be found. The DataObject content is an Object. THis Object may be hold the bytes or it may be an instance of an Identifier, in which can it may point to the location of the bytes, or may point to a physical object.
Author:
david

      Description copied from interface: DataObject
      Get the Object (if any) which makes up the DataObject. The Object may be an instance of an
      • Identifier, in which case it is a pointer to the actual DataObject
      • String, in which case one may try to print it
      • InputStream, in which case this is a Digital Object
      • other specific types which we can deal with
